Sling Blade;;92;;96;;R;;Mentally disabled Karl Childers (Billy Bob Thornton) is released from the mental hospital where he has spent most of his life after murdering his mother and her lover. He soon forms a bond with Frank (Lucas Black), a boy whose father committed suicide. When Frank's mother, Linda (Natalie Canerday), lets Karl stay at their house, her cruel boyfriend, Doyle (Dwight Yoakam), tries to get Karl removed. Determined to protect his friend, Karl devises a way to save Frank from years of Doyle's abuse.;;Drama;;Billy Bob Thornton;;1996;;Billy Bob Thornton,Dwight Yoakam,J.T. Walsh,John Ritter,Lucas Black,Natalie Canerday,James Hampton,Robert Duvall,Rick Dial,Brent Briscoe,Christy Ward,Jim Jarmusch;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/sling_blade